A crafted packet can cause infinite recursion by making the pointer point to itself or create a long chain of valid pointers, resulting in stack exhaustion. The code does not check if the pointer is a valid, non-recursive reference. To fix this vulnerability, you should add a check to ensure the pointer is not recursive or limit the recursion depth to prevent stack exhaustion.

